2}=3D9}"></span>. Also unlike addition and multiplication, exponentiation i=
s not <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Associative" class=3D"mw-red=
irect" title=3D"Associative">associative</a>: for example, <span class=3D"t=
exhtml">(2<sup>3</sup>)<sup>2</sup> =3D 8<sup>2</sup> =3D 64</span>, wherea=
s <span class=3D"texhtml">2<sup>(3<sup>2</sup>)</sup> =3D 2<sup>9</sup> =3D=
 512</span>. Without parentheses, the conventional <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Order_of_operations" title=3D"Order of operations">order o=
f operations</a> for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serial_expone=
ntiation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Serial exponentiation">serial expo=
nentiation</a> in superscript notation is top-down (or <i>right</i>-associa=
tive), not bottom-up<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Bronstein_1987_28-0" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation#cite_note-Bro=
nstein_1987-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<span class=3D"cite-=
