an></span></div>
<p>The powers of a sum can normally be computed from the powers of the summ=
ands by the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binomial_formula" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binomial formula">binomial formula</a>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e (a+b)^{n}=3D\sum _{i=3D0}^{n}{\binom {n}{i}}a^{i}b^{n-i}=3D\sum _{i=3D0}^=
{n}{\frac {n!}{i!(n-i)!}}a^{i}b^{n-i}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>b</mi>
        <msup>
          <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mrow>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-OPEN">
              <mo maxsize=3D"2.047em" minsize=3D"2.047em">(</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mfrac linethickness=3D"0">
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mi>i</mi>
            </mfrac>
            <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-CLOSE">
              <mo maxsize=3D"2.047em" minsize=3D"2.047em">)</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mrow>
        </mrow>
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <munderover>
          <mo>=E2=88=91<!-- =E2=88=91 --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
            <mo>=3D</mo>
            <mn>0</mn>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </munderover>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo>!</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              <mi>i</mi>
              <mo>!</mo>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
              <mi>i</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
              <mo>!</mo>
            </mrow>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <msup>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <msup>
          <mi>b</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle (a+b)^{n}=3D\=
sum _{i=3D0}^{n}{\binom {n}{i}}a^{i}b^{n-i}=3D\sum _{i=3D0}^{n}{\frac {n!}{=
i!(n-i)!}}a^{i}b^{n-i}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/3d288a32615a5b91dc0060530c3df1721a6fa7ac" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -3.005ex; width:49.201ex; height:6.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle (a=
+b)^{n}=3D\sum _{i=3D0}^{n}{\binom {n}{i}}a^{i}b^{n-i}=3D\sum _{i=3D0}^{n}{=
\frac {n!}{i!(n-i)!}}a^{i}b^{n-i}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>However, this formula is true only if the summands commute (i.e. that <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml"><i>ab</i> =3D <i>ba</i></span>), which is implied if =
they belong to a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_structu=
re" title=3D"Algebraic structure">structure</a> that is <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commutative_property" title=3D"Commutative property">=
commutative</a>. Otherwise, if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-s=
tyle:italic;">a</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">b</span> are, say, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squar=
e_matrix" title=3D"Square matrix">square matrices</a> of the same size, thi=
s formula cannot be used. It follows that in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Computer_algebra" title=3D"Computer algebra">computer algebra</a=
>, many <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algorithm" title=3D"Algori=
thm">algorithms</a> involving integer exponents must be changed when the ex=
ponentiation bases do not commute. Some general purpose <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_algebra_system" title=3D"Computer algebra sy=
stem">computer algebra systems</a> use a different notation (sometimes <spa=
n class=3D"texhtml">^^</span> instead of <span class=3D"texhtml">^</span>) =
for exponentiation with non-commuting bases, which is then called <b>non-co=
mmutative exponentiation</b>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Combinatorial_interpretatio=
n">Combinatorial interpretation</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" titl=
e=3D"Edit section: Combinatorial interpretation"><span>edit</span></a><span=
 class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation#Exponenti=
ation_over_sets">Exponentiation over sets</a></div>
<p>For nonnegative integers <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">n</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">m</span>, the value of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i><sup><i>m</i>=
</sup></span> is the number of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fun=
ction_(mathematics)" title=3D"Function (mathematics)">functions</a> from a =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_(mathematics)" title=3D"Set (m=
athematics)">set</a> of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:it=
alic;">m</span> elements to a set of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">n</span> elements (see <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Cardinal_exponentiation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cardinal e=
xponentiation">cardinal exponentiation</a>). Such functions can be represen=
ted as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>-<=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuple" title=3D"Tuple">tuples</a> f=
rom an <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>-e=
lement set (or as <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"=
>m</span>-letter words from an <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-s=
tyle:italic;">n</span>-letter alphabet). Some examples for particular value=
s of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span> and=
 <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span> are giv=
en in the following table:
</p>
<table class=3D"wikitable">
<tbody><tr>
