<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Particular_bases">Particula=
r bases</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExpo=
nentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=3D"Edit section: Parti=
cular bases"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]<=
/span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Powers_of_ten">Powers of te=
n <span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Base_10"></span></h4><span class=3D"mw-edits=
ection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;se=
ction=3D13" title=3D"Edit section: Powers of ten"><span>edit</span></a><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scientific_notation" tit=
le=3D"Scientific notation">Scientific notation</a></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_of_10" title=
=3D"Power of 10">Power of 10</a></div>
<p>In the base ten (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decimal" title=
=3D"Decimal">decimal</a>) number system, integer powers of <span class=3D"t=
exhtml">10</span> are written as the digit <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span>=
 followed or preceded by a number of zeroes determined by the sign and magn=
itude of the exponent. For example, <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"=
nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7003100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>10<su=
p>3</sup></span> =3D <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"700310=
0000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1000</span></span> and <span class=3D"texhtm=
l"><span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"6996100000000000000=E2=
=99=A0"></span>10<sup>=E2=88=924</sup></span> =3D <span class=3D"nowrap"><s=
pan data-sort-value=3D"6996100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>0.0001</span></=
span>.
</p><p>Exponentiation with base <span class=3D"texhtml"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/10_(number)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"10 (numbe=
r)">10</a></span> is used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scien=
tific_notation" title=3D"Scientific notation">scientific notation</a> to de=
note large or small numbers. For instance, <span class=3D"nowrap"><span dat=
a-sort-value=3D"7008299792458000000=E2=99=A0"></span>299<span style=3D"marg=
in-left:.25em;">792</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">458</span>&nbs=
p;m/s</span> (the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speed_of_light" =
title=3D"Speed of light">speed of light</a> in vacuum, in <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metres_per_second" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"M=
etres per second">metres per second</a>) can be written as <span class=3D"n=
owrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7008299792458000000=E2=99=A0"></span>2.997<=
span style=3D"margin-left:.25em;">924</span><span style=3D"margin-left:.25e=
m;">58</span><span style=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97=
</span>10<sup>8</sup>&nbsp;m/s</span> and then <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Approximation" title=3D"Approximation">approximated</a> as <sp=
an class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7008299800000000000=E2=99=A0">=
</span>2.998<span style=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97<=
/span>10<sup>8</sup>&nbsp;m/s</span>.
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SI_prefix" class=3D"mw-redi=
rect" title=3D"SI prefix">SI prefixes</a> based on powers of <span class=3D=
"texhtml">10</span> are also used to describe small or large quantities. Fo=
r example, the prefix <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kilo-" title=
=3D"Kilo-">kilo</a> means <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"nowrap"><s=
pan data-sort-value=3D"7003100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>10<sup>3</sup><=
/span> =3D <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7003100000000000=
000=E2=99=A0"></span>1000</span></span>, so a kilometre is <span class=3D"n=
owrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"7003100000000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>1000&n=
bsp;m</span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Powers_of_two"><span class=
=3D"anchor" id=3D"Base_2"></span>Powers of two</h4><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;sec=
tion=3D14" title=3D"Edit section: Powers of two"><span>edit</span></a><span=
 class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_of_two" title=
=3D"Power of two">Power of two</a></div>
<p>The first negative powers of <span class=3D"texhtml">2</span> have speci=
al names: <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cl=
ass=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;=
"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displayst=
yle 2^{-1}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2^{-1}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/e4d1095a62660b99f5e9ef85ade17ab11a5d909f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:3.495ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2^{=
-1}}"></span>is a <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_half" tit=
le=3D"One half">half</a></i>; <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elem=
ent-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" sty=
le=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" al=
ttext=3D"{\displaystyle 2^{-2}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>2</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2^{-2}}</anno=
tation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/4894401ca84c8f24cc9d94fa8aa516d1a1bc9497" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:3.495ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2^{=
-2}}"></span> is a <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/4_(number)" =
class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"4 (number)">quarter</a>.</i>
</p><p>Powers of <span class=3D"texhtml">2</span> appear in <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Set_theory" title=3D"Set theory">set theory</a>, =
since a set with <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> members has a <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Power_set" title=3D"Power set">power s=
et</a>, the set of all of its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subs=
et" title=3D"Subset">subsets</a>, which has <span class=3D"texhtml">2<sup><=
i>n</i></sup></span> members.
</p><p>Integer powers of <span class=3D"texhtml">2</span> are important in =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computer_science" title=3D"Compute=
r science">computer science</a>. The positive integer powers <span class=3D=
"texhtml">2<sup><i>n</i></sup></span> give the number of possible values fo=
r an <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span>-<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Bit" title=3D"Bit">bit</a> integer <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Binary_number" title=3D"Binary number">binary number</a>; for e=
xample, a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byte" title=3D"Byte">byt=
e</a> may take <span class=3D"texhtml">2<sup>8</sup> =3D 256</span> differe=
nt values. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_number_syste=
m" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binary number system">binary number syste=
m</a> expresses any number as a sum of powers of <span class=3D"texhtml">2<=
/span>, and denotes it as a sequence of <span class=3D"texhtml">0</span> an=
d <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span>, separated by a <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Binary_point" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binary point"=
>binary point</a>, where <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span> indicates a power=
 of <span class=3D"texhtml">2</span> that appears in the sum; the exponent =
is determined by the place of this <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span>: the no=
nnegative exponents are the rank of the <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span> on=
 the left of the point (starting from <span class=3D"texhtml">0</span>), an=
d the negative exponents are determined by the rank on the right of the poi=
nt.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Powers_of_one">Powers of on=
e</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponentia=
tion&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D15" title=3D"Edit section: Powers of o=
ne"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></s=
pan></div>
<p>Every power of one equals: <span class=3D"texhtml">1<sup><i>n</i></sup> =
=3D 1</span>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Powers_of_zero">Powers of z=
ero</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracke=
t">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponent=
iation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" title=3D"Edit section: Powers of=
 zero"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span>=
</span></div>
<p>For a positive exponent <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> &gt; 0</span>, =
the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>th po=
wer of zero is zero: <span class=3D"texhtml">0<sup><i>n</i></sup> =3D 0</sp=
an>. For a negative exponent, <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elem=
ent-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" sty=
le=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" al=
ttext=3D"{\displaystyle 0^{-n}=3D1/0^{n}=3D1/0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msup>
          <mn>0</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <msup>
          <mn>0</mn>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msup>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mn>0</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 0^{-n}=3D1/0^=
{n}=3D1/0}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
