mplex number <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>i</i></span>, see <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation#nth_roots_of_a_complex_number">=C2=
=A7&nbsp;nth roots of a complex number</a>.
</p><div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Large_exponents">Large =
exponents</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DEx=
ponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Lar=
ge exponents"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]=
</span></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Limit_of_a_sequence" title=
=3D"Limit of a sequence">limit of a sequence</a> of powers of a number grea=
ter than one diverges; in other words, the sequence grows without bound:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>n</i></sup> =E2=86=92 =E2=
=88=9E</span> as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=86=92 =E2=88=9E</span=
> when <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i> &gt; 1</span></dd></dl>
<p>This can be read as "<i>b</i> to the power of <i>n</i> tends to <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_real_number_line" title=3D"Exten=
ded real number line">+=E2=88=9E</a> as <i>n</i> tends to infinity when <i>=
b</i> is greater than one".
</p><p>Powers of a number with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abs=
olute_value" title=3D"Absolute value">absolute value</a> less than one tend=
 to zero:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>n</i></sup> =E2=86=92 0</sp=
an> as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=86=92 =E2=88=9E</span> when <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml">|<span class=3D"nowrap" style=3D"padding-left:0.1em; p=
adding-right:0.1em;"><i>b</i></span>| &lt; 1</span></dd></dl>
<p>Any power of one is always one:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>n</i></sup> =3D 1</span> fo=
r all <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> for <span class=3D"texhtml"><=
i>b</i> =3D 1</span></dd></dl>
<p>Powers of a negative number <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-ele=
ment-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" st=
yle=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" a=
lttext=3D"{\displaystyle b\leq -1}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo>=E2=89=A4<!-- =E2=89=A4 --></mo>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle b\leq -1}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f60e3adeea8aef80481c94cf32a5c0ac2f4a9a98" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.505ex; width:7.067ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle b\l=
eq -1}"></span> alternate between positive and negative as <span class=3D"t=
exhtml"><i>n</i></span> alternates between even and odd, and thus do not te=
nd to any limit as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i></span> grows.
</p><p>If the exponentiated number varies while tending to <span class=3D"t=
exhtml">1</span> as the exponent tends to infinity, then the limit is not n=
ecessarily one of those above. A particularly important case is
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"texhtml">(1 + 1/<i>n</i>)<sup><i>n</i></sup> =E2=86=
=92 <i>e</i></span> as <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>n</i> =E2=86=92 =E2=88=9E=
</span></dd></dl>
<p>See <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation#Exponential_=
function">=C2=A7&nbsp;Exponential function</a> below.
</p><p>Other limits, in particular those of expressions that take on an <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indeterminate_form" title=3D"Indeterm=
inate form">indeterminate form</a>, are described in <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation#Limits_of_powers">=C2=A7&nbsp;Limits of p=
owers</a> below.
</p>
