</p><p>If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">r</span=
> is a positive rational number, <span class=3D"texhtml">0<sup><i>r</i></su=
p> =3D 0</span>, by definition.
</p><p>All these definitions are required for extending the identity <span =
class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-=
mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D=
"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle (x^{r})^{s}=
=3Dx^{rs}}">
