arithm">logarithm</a> function. Specifically, the fact that the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_logarithm" title=3D"Natural logarithm=
">natural logarithm</a> <span class=3D"texhtml">ln(<i>x</i>)</span> is the =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_function" title=3D"Inverse=
 function">inverse</a> of the exponential function <span class=3D"texhtml">=
<i>e</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> means that one has
</p>
