<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Non-integer_exponents_with_=
a_complex_base">Non-integer exponents with a complex base</h2><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=
=3Dedit&amp;section=3D27" title=3D"Edit section: Non-integer exponents with=
 a complex base"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket=
">]</span></span></div>
<p>In the preceding sections, exponentiation with non-integer exponents has=
 been defined for positive real bases only. For other bases, difficulties a=
ppear already with the apparently simple case of <span class=3D"texhtml mva=
r" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>th roots, that is, of exponents <sp=
an class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-ma=
th-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=
=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle 1/n,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mo>/</mo>
        </mrow>
        <mi>n</mi>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 1/n,}</annota=
tion>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/de8b6b7358e7a75273d3a0612d1ef0dcedb77730" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:4.366ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 1/n=
,}"></span> where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;"=
>n</span> is a positive integer. Although the general theory of exponentiat=
ion with non-integer exponents applies to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" styl=
e=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>th roots, this case deserves to be conside=
red first, since it does not need to use <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Complex_logarithm" title=3D"Complex logarithm">complex logarithms</a=
>, and is therefore easier to understand.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"nth_roots_of_a_complex_numb=
er"><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>th ro=
ots of a complex number</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"m=
w-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.=
php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D28" title=3D"Edi=
t section: nth roots of a complex number"><span>edit</span></a><span class=
=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Every nonzero complex number <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-=
style:italic;">z</span> may be written in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Polar_form" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Polar form">polar form</=
a> as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e z=3D\rho e^{i\theta }=3D\rho (\cos \theta +i\sin \theta ),}">
