<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Irrationality_and_transcend=
ence">Irrationality and transcendence</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/w/index.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D36=
" title=3D"Edit section: Irrationality and transcendence"><span>edit</span>=
</a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gelfond%E2%80%93Schn=
eider_theorem" title=3D"Gelfond=E2=80=93Schneider theorem">Gelfond=E2=80=93=
Schneider theorem</a></div>
<p>If <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> is=
 a positive real <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_number"=
 title=3D"Algebraic number">algebraic number</a>, and <span class=3D"texhtm=
l mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> is a rational number, then <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> is an algebraic nu=
mber. This results from the theory of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Algebraic_extension" title=3D"Algebraic extension">algebraic extensions=
</a>. This remains true if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">b</span> is any algebraic number, in which case, all values of <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>x</i></sup></span> (as a <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multivalued_function" title=3D"Multivalued fun=
ction">multivalued function</a>) are algebraic. If <span class=3D"texhtml m=
var" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> is <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Irrational_number" title=3D"Irrational number">irrational</a> (=
that is, <i>not rational</i>), and both <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;">x</span> are algebraic, Gelfond=E2=80=93Schneider theor=
em asserts that all values of <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><i>x</i>=
</sup></span> are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Transcendental_n=
umber" title=3D"Transcendental number">transcendental</a> (that is, not alg=
ebraic), except if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;=
">b</span> equals <span class=3D"texhtml">0</span> or <span class=3D"texhtm=
l">1</span>.
</p><p>In other words, if <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">x</span> is irrational and <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-mat=
h-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11=
y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/Math=
ML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle b\not \in \{0,1\},}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo>=E2=88=89</mo>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">{</mo>
        <mn>0</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">}</mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle b\not \in \{0=
,1\},}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/146d85efbc22f5f38c9bc8556198014ed26494dd" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:10.169ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle b\=
not \in \{0,1\},}"></span> then at least one of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar=
" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>b</i><sup><=
i>x</i></sup></span> is transcendental.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Integer_powers_in_algebra">=
Integer powers in algebra</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/inde=
x.php?title=3DExponentiation&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D37" title=3D"E=
dit section: Integer powers in algebra"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The definition of exponentiation with positive integer exponents as repe=
ated multiplication may apply to any <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Associative_operation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Associative operat=
ion">associative operation</a> denoted as a multiplication.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-39" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expone=
ntiation#cite_note-39"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>nb 2<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The definition of <span class=3D"texht=
ml"><i>x</i><sup>0</sup></span> requires further the existence of a <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplicative_identity" class=3D"mw-redi=
rect" title=3D"Multiplicative identity">multiplicative identity</a>.<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-40" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Exponentiation#cite_note-40"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>38<spa=
n class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>An <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Algebraic_structure" tit=
le=3D"Algebraic structure">algebraic structure</a> consisting of a set toge=
ther with an associative operation denoted multiplicatively, and a multipli=
cative identity denoted by <span class=3D"texhtml">1</span> is a <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monoid" title=3D"Monoid">monoid</a>. In such=
 a monoid, exponentiation of an element <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> is defined inductively by
</p>
