n G}"></span> and every integer <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-=
style:italic;">n</span>.
</p><p>The set of all powers of an element of a group form a <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subgroup" title=3D"Subgroup">subgroup</a>. A gro=
up (or subgroup) that consists of all powers of a specific element <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> is the <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclic_group" title=3D"Cyclic group">cycl=
ic group</a> generated by <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">x</span>. If all the powers of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">x</span> are distinct, the group is <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isomorphic" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Isomor=
phic">isomorphic</a> to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Additi=
ve_group" title=3D"Additive group">additive group</a> <span class=3D"mwe-ma=
th-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline m=
we-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.=
org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \mathbb {Z} }">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
